def: A rural poem; a poetical composition on husbandry, containingrules for cultivating lands, etc.; as, the Georgics of Virgil.
Any disease or symptoms of disease referable to disorders ofthe brain; as, lead encephalopathy, the cerebral symptoms attendingchronic lead poisoning.
Not cyclic; not disposed in cycles or whorls; as: (a) (Bot.)
To present again; as, to re-present the points of an argument.
In a swift manner; with quick motion or velocity; fleetly.Wyclif.

Containing or expressing salutations; speaking a welcome;greeting; -- applied especially to the oration which introduces theexercises of the Commencements, or similar public exhibitions, inAmerican colleges.
That which serves to anoint; any soft unctuous substance usedfor smearing or anointing; an unguent.
The office or employment of an accountant.
The quality or state of being a vagrant; a wandering without asettled home; an unsettled condition; vagabondism.Threatened away into banishment and vagrancy. Barrow.

A noncommissioned officer, next below a sergeant. In the UnitedStates army he is the lowest noncomissioned officer in a company ofinfantry. He places and relieves sentinels. Corporal's guard, adetachment such as would be in charge of a corporal for guard duty,etc.; hence, derisively, a very small number of persons.-- Lance corporal, an assistant corporal on private's pay. Farrow.-- Ship's corporal (Naut.), a petty officer who assists the masterat arms in his various duties.
